<h2>How to add a product page</h2>
<p>
  From your Prowl dashboard, click <strong>"Add product page"</strong>. You'll see a list of products from your Shopify catalog. Select the product you want to monitor and it will be added to your monitoring list.
</p>

<h2>How many pages can I monitor?</h2>
<p>
  You can monitor up to <strong>3 product pages</strong> at a time. If you need to monitor a different product, remove one of your existing pages first and then add the new one.
</p>

<h2>Which pages should I monitor?</h2>
<p>
  We recommend prioritizing:
</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Your highest-traffic products</strong> — issues here affect the most customers.</li>
  <li><strong>Your highest-revenue products</strong> — a broken page here has the biggest impact on sales.</li>
  <li><strong>Products with complex variants</strong> — pages with many size/color/style options are more likely to have variant selector issues.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Removing a product page</h2>
<p>
  To stop monitoring a page, click on it from the Product Pages list and select <strong>"Remove"</strong>. The page and its scan history will be removed from your dashboard. You can re-add the same product later if needed.
</p>
